\q1 And every fool shall be taken therewith.
\q1
\v 8 Blessed is the rich that is found without blemish,
\q1 And that goes not after gold.
\q1
\v 9 Who is he? and we will call him blessed:
\q1 For wonderful things has he done among his people.
\q1
\v 10 Who has been tried by it, and found perfect?
\q1 Then let him glory.
\q1 Who has had the power to transgress, and has not transgressed?
\q1 And to do evil, and has not done it?
\q1
\v 11 His goods shall be made sure,
\q1 And the congregation shall declare his alms.
\q1
