\q1 And say not, Many are the things upon it.
\q1
\v 13 Remember that an evil eye is a wicked thing:
\q1 What has been created more evil than an eye?
\q1 Therefore it sheds tears from every face.
\q1
\v 14 Stretch not your hand wherever it looks,
\q1 And thrust not yourself with it into the dish.
\q1
\v 15 Consider your neighbor’s \add liking \add* by your own;
\q1 And be discreet in every point.
\q1
\v 16 Eat, as \add becomes \add* a man, those things which are set before you;
\q1 And eat not greedily, lest you be hated.
\q1
\v 17 Be first to leave off for manners’ sake;
\q1 And be not insatiable, lest you offend.
\q1
\v 18 And if you sit among many,
\q1 Reach not out your hand before them.
