\q1
\v 19 How sufficient to a well-mannered man is a very little,
\q1 And he does not breathe hard upon his bed.
\q1
\v 20 Healthy sleep comes of moderate eating;
\q1 He rises early, and his wits are with him:
\q1 The pain of wakefulness, and colic,
\q1 And griping, are with an insatiable man.
\q1
\v 21 And if you have been forced to eat,
\q1 Rise up in the midst thereof, and you shall have rest.
\q1
